Floral Apostle
--------------

Winter daffodil
Stalwart sentinel
Guardian of hope
Humble antidote
To our brumal ill

(Here is a call for the endurance…)

Your golden bloom
Under skies cold and grey
Pierces dark and gloom
Speaks of a better day

Though storm battered
And snow covered
Indomitable yellow
A bright foreshadow
Of sun assured

(Here is a call for the endurance…)

Your steadfast constant cheer
Banishes our dismay
Leaves no space for despair
Shows us the better day

Winter may linger
Last many a year
Floral apostle
Will you then please tell
What we need to hear

(Here is a call for the endurance…)

Your resolute message
The sure hope you relay
Sweetens bitter passage
Towards that better day

Of this we are sure
Remind our hearts again
If we will endure
With Him we will reign

Show Jerusalem
The city to come
City where the dark
Can't stay, cannot park
It's lit by the Son

Show Jerusalem
The city to come
City where the dark
